# Frontend Testing Rules

## Runner and libraries
- **Vitest**, not Jest — this repo builds with Vite, and Vitest shares its config/transform
  pipeline. Don't introduce Jest or `ts-jest`.
- **React Testing Library** (`@testing-library/react` + `@testing-library/jest-dom`) for
  component tests. Query by role/label/text (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`) the way a user
  or screen reader would — reach for `data-testid` only when no accessible query exists.
- **MSW** (Mock Service Worker) to mock `packages/api-client` HTTP calls in tests, instead
  of manually stubbing `fetch` or the React Query client. Keeps tests close to real network
  behavior and avoids brittle mock wiring per test file.

## File layout and naming
- Colocate tests next to the source file: `Button.tsx` -> `Button.test.tsx`,
  `usePrompts.ts` -> `usePrompts.test.ts`. Don't create a parallel `__tests__/` tree.
- One `vitest.config.ts` per app (or a shared base extended per app) — don't rely on a
  single root config to cover every app's path aliases and federation setup.
- Wire the `test` script into `turbo.json` so `pnpm test` at the root runs every app/package
  in Turbo's dependency order, the same way `build`/`typecheck` already do.

## What to test
- **`packages/ui`**: token/preset exports and shared component behavior (props, variants,
  accessibility attributes) — this is the base layer every MFE depends on, regressions here
  are the highest blast radius.
- **`packages/api-client`**: hook behavior against mocked responses (loading/error/success
  states), not the implementation details of the underlying fetch wrapper.
- **Each app (`apps/*`)**: component and page-level behavior for that app's own domain
  (prompt CRUD forms, guardrail rule builder, usage dashboard, etc.) — not Module Federation
  wiring itself.
- **Module Federation boundaries**: don't spin up other remotes in unit tests to test the
  dashboard host's remote loader. Mock the federated import boundary (e.g. mock the dynamic
  `import()` a remote entry resolves to) and test the Suspense/error-boundary behavior in
  isolation — see `.cursor/rules/module-federation.mdc` for the loader contract.

## Style
- Prefer explicit assertions (`expect(screen.getByText("Active")).toBeInTheDocument()`) over
  snapshot testing. Snapshots are acceptable for small, stable markup (e.g. an SVG icon
  wrapper) but should not be the primary assertion style for interactive components.
- Test user-visible behavior and outcomes, not internal state or implementation details —
  if a refactor that doesn't change behavior breaks the test, the test is testing the wrong
  thing.
- Every new component/hook added under `packages/ui`, `packages/api-client`, or any
  `apps/*/src/components/**` should ship with at least one test in the same PR — don't defer
  tests to a follow-up.
